23size_t hash_value(OutputFrameStateCombine const& sc) {
24 return base::hash_value(sc.parameter_);
25}
26
27std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, OutputFrameStateCombine const& sc) {
28 if (sc.parameter_ == OutputFrameStateCombine::kInvalidIndex)
29 return os << "Ignore";
30 return os << "PokeAt(" << sc.parameter_ << ")";
31}

33bool operator==(FrameStateInfo const& lhs, FrameStateInfo const& rhs) {
34 return lhs.type() == rhs.type() && lhs.bailout_id() == rhs.bailout_id() &&
35 lhs.state_combine() == rhs.state_combine() &&
36 lhs.function_info() == rhs.function_info();
37}
38
39bool operator!=(FrameStateInfo const& lhs, FrameStateInfo const& rhs) {
40 return !(lhs == rhs);
41}
42
43size_t hash_value(FrameStateInfo const& info) {
44 return base::hash_combine(static_cast<int>(info.type()), info.bailout_id(),
45 info.state_combine());
46}

48std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, FrameStateType type) {
49 switch (type) {
50 case FrameStateType::kUnoptimizedFunction:
51 os << "UNOPTIMIZED_FRAME";
52 break;
53 case FrameStateType::kInlinedExtraArguments:
54 os << "INLINED_EXTRA_ARGUMENTS";
55 break;
56 case FrameStateType::kConstructCreateStub:
57 os << "CONSTRUCT_CREATE_STUB";
58 break;
59 case FrameStateType::kConstructInvokeStub:
60 os << "CONSTRUCT_INVOKE_STUB";
61 break;
62 case FrameStateType::kBuiltinContinuation:
63 os << "BUILTIN_CONTINUATION_FRAME";
64 break;
65#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
66 case FrameStateType::kWasmInlinedIntoJS:
67 os << "WASM_INLINED_INTO_JS_FRAME";
68 break;
69 case FrameStateType::kJSToWasmBuiltinContinuation:
70 os << "JS_TO_WASM_BUILTIN_CONTINUATION_FRAME";
71 break;
72 case FrameStateType::kLiftoffFunction:
73 os << "LIFTOFF_FRAME";
74 break;
75#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
76 case FrameStateType::kJavaScriptBuiltinContinuation:
77 os << "JAVA_SCRIPT_BUILTIN_CONTINUATION_FRAME";
78 break;
79 case FrameStateType::kJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationWithCatch:
80 os << "JAVA_SCRIPT_BUILTIN_CONTINUATION_WITH_CATCH_FRAME";
81 break;
82 }
83 return os;
84}

86std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, FrameStateInfo const& info) {
87 os << info.type() << ", " << info.bailout_id() << ", "
88 << info.state_combine();
89 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info;
90 if (info.shared_info().ToHandle(&shared_info)) {
91 os << ", " << Brief(*shared_info);
92 }
93 return os;
94}

98// Lazy deopt points where the frame state is associated with a call get an
99// additional parameter for the return result from the call. The return result
100// is added by the deoptimizer and not explicitly specified in the frame state.
101// Lazy deopt points which can catch exceptions further get an additional
102// parameter, namely the exception thrown. The exception is also added by the
103// deoptimizer.
104uint8_t DeoptimizerParameterCountFor(ContinuationFrameStateMode mode) {
105 switch (mode) {
106 case ContinuationFrameStateMode::EAGER:
107 return 0;
108 case ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY:
109 return 1;
110 case ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY_WITH_CATCH:
111 return 2;
112 }
113 UNREACHABLE();
114}
115
116FrameState CreateBuiltinContinuationFrameStateCommon(
117 JSGraph* jsgraph, FrameStateType frame_type, Builtin name, Node* closure,
118 Node* context, Node** parameters, int parameter_count,
119 Node* outer_frame_state,
120 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = Handle<SharedFunctionInfo>(),
121 const wasm::FunctionSig* signature = nullptr) {
122 Graph* const graph = jsgraph->graph();
123 CommonOperatorBuilder* const common = jsgraph->common();
124
125 const Operator* op_param =
126 common->StateValues(parameter_count, SparseInputMask::Dense());
127 Node* params_node = graph->NewNode(op_param, parameter_count, parameters);
128
129 BytecodeOffset bailout_id = Builtins::GetContinuationBytecodeOffset(name);
130#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
131 const FrameStateFunctionInfo* state_info =
132 signature ? common->CreateJSToWasmFrameStateFunctionInfo(
133 frame_type, parameter_count, 0, shared, signature)
134 : common->CreateFrameStateFunctionInfo(
135 frame_type, parameter_count, 0, shared);
136#else
137 DCHECK_NULL(signature);
138 const FrameStateFunctionInfo* state_info =
139 common->CreateFrameStateFunctionInfo(frame_type, parameter_count, 0,
140 shared);
141#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
142
143 const Operator* op = common->FrameState(
144 bailout_id, OutputFrameStateCombine::Ignore(), state_info);
145 return FrameState(graph->NewNode(op, params_node, jsgraph->EmptyStateValues(),
146 jsgraph->EmptyStateValues(), context,
147 closure, outer_frame_state));
148}

152FrameState CreateStubBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
153 JSGraph* jsgraph, Builtin name, Node* context, Node* const* parameters,
154 int parameter_count, Node* outer_frame_state,
155 ContinuationFrameStateMode mode, const wasm::FunctionSig* signature) {
156 Callable callable = Builtins::CallableFor(jsgraph->isolate(), name);
157 CallInterfaceDescriptor descriptor = callable.descriptor();
158
159 std::vector<Node*> actual_parameters;
160 // Stack parameters first. Depending on {mode}, final parameters are added
161 // by the deoptimizer and aren't explicitly passed in the frame state.
162 int stack_parameter_count =
163 descriptor.GetStackParameterCount() - DeoptimizerParameterCountFor(mode);
164
165 // Ensure the parameters added by the deoptimizer are passed on the stack.
166 // This check prevents using TFS builtins as continuations while doing the
167 // lazy deopt. Use TFC or TFJ builtin as a lazy deopt continuation which
168 // would pass the result parameter on the stack.
169 DCHECK_GE(stack_parameter_count, 0);
170
171 // Reserving space in the vector.
172 actual_parameters.reserve(stack_parameter_count +
173 descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount());
174 for (int i = 0; i < stack_parameter_count; ++i) {
175 actual_parameters.push_back(
176 parameters[descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount() + i]);
177 }
178 // Register parameters follow, context will be added by instruction selector
179 // during FrameState translation.
180 for (int i = 0; i < descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount(); ++i) {
181 actual_parameters.push_back(parameters[i]);
182 }
183
184 FrameStateType frame_state_type = FrameStateType::kBuiltinContinuation;
185#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
186 if (name == Builtin::kJSToWasmLazyDeoptContinuation) {
187 CHECK_NOT_NULL(signature);
188 frame_state_type = FrameStateType::kJSToWasmBuiltinContinuation;
189 }
190#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
191 return CreateBuiltinContinuationFrameStateCommon(
192 jsgraph, frame_state_type, name, jsgraph->UndefinedConstant(), context,
193 actual_parameters.data(), static_cast<int>(actual_parameters.size()),
194 outer_frame_state, Handle<SharedFunctionInfo>(), signature);
195}
196
197#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
198FrameState CreateJSWasmCallBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
199 JSGraph* jsgraph, Node* context, Node* outer_frame_state,
200 const wasm::FunctionSig* signature) {
201 base::Optional<wasm::ValueKind> wasm_return_kind =
202 wasm::WasmReturnTypeFromSignature(signature);
203 Node* node_return_type =
204 jsgraph->SmiConstant(wasm_return_kind ? wasm_return_kind.value() : -1);
205 Node* lazy_deopt_parameters[] = {node_return_type};
206 return CreateStubBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
207 jsgraph, Builtin::kJSToWasmLazyDeoptContinuation, context,
208 lazy_deopt_parameters, arraysize(lazy_deopt_parameters),
209 outer_frame_state, ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY, signature);
210}
211#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY

213FrameState CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
214 JSGraph* jsgraph, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared, Builtin name, Node* target,
215 Node* context, Node* const* stack_parameters, int stack_parameter_count,
216 Node* outer_frame_state, ContinuationFrameStateMode mode) {
217 // Depending on {mode}, final parameters are added by the deoptimizer
218 // and aren't explicitly passed in the frame state.
219 DCHECK_EQ(Builtins::GetStackParameterCount(name),
220 stack_parameter_count + DeoptimizerParameterCountFor(mode));
221
222 Node* argc = jsgraph->ConstantNoHole(Builtins::GetStackParameterCount(name));
223
224 // Stack parameters first. They must be first because the receiver is expected
225 // to be the second value in the translation when creating stack crawls
226 // (e.g. Error.stack) of optimized JavaScript frames.
227 std::vector<Node*> actual_parameters;
228 actual_parameters.reserve(stack_parameter_count);
229 for (int i = 0; i < stack_parameter_count; ++i) {
230 actual_parameters.push_back(stack_parameters[i]);
231 }
232
233 Node* new_target = jsgraph->UndefinedConstant();
234
235 // Register parameters follow stack parameters. The context will be added by
236 // instruction selector during FrameState translation.
237 actual_parameters.push_back(target); // kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister
238 actual_parameters.push_back(new_target); // kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister
239 actual_parameters.push_back(argc); // kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister
240
241 return CreateBuiltinContinuationFrameStateCommon(
242 jsgraph,
243 mode == ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY_WITH_CATCH
244 ? FrameStateType::kJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationWithCatch
245 : FrameStateType::kJavaScriptBuiltinContinuation,
246 name, target, context, &actual_parameters[0],
247 static_cast<int>(actual_parameters.size()), outer_frame_state,
248 shared.object());
249}
250
251FrameState CreateGenericLazyDeoptContinuationFrameState(
252 JSGraph* graph, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared, Node* target, Node* context,
253 Node* receiver, Node* outer_frame_state) {
254 Node* stack_parameters[]{receiver};
255 const int stack_parameter_count = arraysize(stack_parameters);
256 return CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
257 graph, shared, Builtin::kGenericLazyDeoptContinuation, target, context,
258 stack_parameters, stack_parameter_count, outer_frame_state,
259 ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
260}
261
262Node* CreateInlinedApiFunctionFrameState(JSGraph* graph,
263 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
264 Node* target, Node* context,
265 Node* receiver,
266 Node* outer_frame_state) {
267 if (!v8_flags.experimental_stack_trace_frames) return outer_frame_state;
268 return CreateGenericLazyDeoptContinuationFrameState(
269 graph, shared, target, context, receiver, outer_frame_state);
270}

272FrameState CloneFrameState(JSGraph* jsgraph, FrameState frame_state,
273 OutputFrameStateCombine changed_state_combine) {
274 Graph* graph = jsgraph->graph();
275 CommonOperatorBuilder* common = jsgraph->common();
276
277 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kFrameState, frame_state->op()->opcode());
278
279 const Operator* op = common->FrameState(
280 frame_state.frame_state_info().bailout_id(), changed_state_combine,
281 frame_state.frame_state_info().function_info());
282 return FrameState(
283 graph->NewNode(op, frame_state.parameters(), frame_state.locals(),
284 frame_state.stack(), frame_state.context(),
285 frame_state.function(), frame_state.outer_frame_state()));
286}
